<br>
But back to the subject of the trade skill devices....<br>
<br>
All they do in increase the skill level that the sucess rate check aginst.  So if you had 100 skill in say Tailoring and you had a Tailoring Device your skill would check as if you had 105.  Now if the item you were making trivialized at say 102, you would still have a chance to get a skill increase because your true skill is 100, but you would have the sucess rate as if you were 105. <p>--Gihmle Gearbungler--
